A number is called a Harshad number if it is divisible by the sum of its digits.
For example, 18 → 1 + 8 = 9 → 18 is divisible by 9 → Harshad.
Input Format

An integer n
Constraints

1≤𝑛≤10^9
Output Format

Print Harshad Number if it is divisible by the sum of its digits, otherwise print Not Harshad Number
Sample Input 0

18
Sample Output 0

Harshad Number
Sample Input 1

23
Sample Output 1

Not Harshad Number

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int n=sc.nextInt();
        int original=n;
        int sum=0;
        while(n>0){
            sum+=n%10;
            n=n/10;
        }
        if(original%sum==0){
            System.out.println("Harshad Number");
        }else{
            System.out.println("Not Harshad Number");
        }
    }
}
